## ESP8266 vs ESP32 (quick reality check)

| Feature   | ESP8266 (yours) | ESP32           |
| --------- | --------------- | --------------- |
| Wi-Fi     | ‚úÖ Yes           | ‚úÖ Yes           |
| Bluetooth | ‚ùå No            | ‚úÖ Yes           |
| CPU       | Single-core     | Dual-core       |
| GPIO pins | Fewer           | More            |
| Power     | Low             | Slightly higher |

üëâ **Important:**
If your project needs **Bluetooth (HC-05 replacement)** ‚Üí ‚ùå ESP8266 **cannot do Bluetooth**
ESP32 **can**.

---

## What you CAN do with your ESP8266

Your ESP8266 is still powerful üí™

You can:

* Replace **HC-05 Bluetooth communication** with **Wi-Fi**
* Send data from helmet ‚Üí bike using:

  * Wi-Fi (HTTP / TCP)
  * ESP-NOW (fast, low-latency)
* Read:

  * Ultrasonic sensor
  * Alcohol sensor
  * Control relays, motors

---

## What you CANNOT do

* ‚ùå No Bluetooth pairing
* ‚ùå Cannot directly replace HC-05 Bluetooth logic

---

## For your Smart Helmet project (important advice)

Since you have:

* 2 √ó HC-05
* 1 √ó ESP8266
* Arduino Uno & Nano

### Best combo (simple & reliable):

* **Arduino + HC-05** ‚Üí Helmet ‚Üî Bike (Bluetooth)
* **ESP8266** ‚Üí Optional Wi-Fi features (IoT / cloud / app)

OR

### Advanced version:

* **ESP8266 ‚Üî ESP8266 (ESP-NOW)**
  (no Bluetooth at all)
